2
Professional services — high-value · per engagement
The new edition is not just a document update — it is a service trigger. Every client who upgrades needs to remap their equipment registers. Every operator moving to function-based management needs a data model redesign. Every team needs training. These engagements are not optional add-ons: they are the natural consequence of adopting a revised standard across a live fleet or shipyard. With 6,000+ vessels in the installed base, the addressable PS market is substantial.
REMAPPING
Equipment register recoding
Every client upgrading to the new edition needs to reclassify their existing component lists. The r4 migration from retired PG9 codes (972–992) to 483xxx creates a concrete, non-deferrable remapping requirement for every dredging and offshore client. Managed as a structured PS engagement per vessel or fleet, with clear scope and deliverables.
$5,000 – 20,000 / engagement
TRANSFORMATION
Component-unit to function management
Many clients still manage equipment at component level — a model that limits predictive maintenance, compliance reporting and lifecycle analysis. The extended SFI structure enables function-based management cleanly. SpecTec is uniquely positioned to lead this transformation: data model redesign, system reconfiguration, AMOS migration and change management.
$15,000 – 60,000 / project
TRAINING
Training & best practices
Maintenance engineers, classification specialists and fleet managers all need structured training on the new code domains. Online or in-person programmes covering emission reduction, dredging and offshore classification, correct application methodology, and SFI best practices for AMOS and AMOS Web. Scalable from individual certification to fleet-wide rollout.
$800 – 2,000 / participant
3
Model evolution — recurring · platform play
The infrastructure already built — public consultation site, GitHub-backed version control, live deployment pipeline — is the foundation of a much larger opportunity. The commercial model can evolve from one-time licence sales into a recurring subscription, and the consultation platform can grow into a full SFI portal. A Q4-2026 release is already planned, adding alternative fuels, shore power, ballast water treatment and ROV systems.
SUBSCRIPTION MODEL
Annual SFI subscription
Replace one-time perpetual licences with an annual subscription covering every future update — Q4-2026 and beyond — plus early access to new appendices and priority participation in consultations. Converts a transactional relationship into a predictable recurring revenue stream, eliminates the "buy and forget" dynamic, and keeps clients engaged year-round.
$1,500 – 4,000 / client / year
PLATFORM
SFI portal
A dedicated web portal for SFI users: full searchable code database, vessel-specific code lookup, proposal submission for new codes, participation in active consultations, and access to classification guidance. Built on top of the existing public site and GitHub infrastructure already in place. Tiered access — free read-only for all, paid tiers for write access, early drafts and API access.
$500 – 2,000 / org / year
